title: PPPP’s  Mirullah Baksh Talpur  wins PS- 69 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Mirullah Baksh Talpur has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-69, Badin-II, by securing 38,759 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Mir Abdullah Khan, of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged a vote 33,378.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 43.35 %.
